https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/bQBFIwb77jrsXiH7TQVFu7onwN7.jpg On a high mountain plain lives a lamb with wool of such remarkable sheen that he breaks into high-steppin' dance. But there comes a day when he loses his lustrous coat and, along with it, his pride. It takes a wise jackalope - a horn-adorned rabbit - to teach the moping lamb that wooly or not, it's what's inside that'll help him rebound from life's troubles. Boundin'
